The paper discusses the use of machine learning to optimize tree search algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also provides sample complexity guarantees, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of partitioning techniques and the optimization of tree size are topics that fall under data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the practical benefits of learning to branch, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
